## Apache 2.0 and CC-BY-SA 4.0 License (wordfreq components)

The following components are derived from the wordfreq project and retain their
original licensing:

- js/wordfreq.js (JavaScript port of wordfreq)
- data/large_en.msgpack.gz (wordfreq data file)

### Apache License 2.0 (wordfreq code)

The wordfreq code is licensed under the Apache License 2.0.
See: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

### Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 (wordfreq data)

The wordfreq data files are licensed under CC-BY-SA 4.0.
See: https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/

**Citation for wordfreq:**

Robyn Speer. (2022). rspeer/wordfreq: v3.0 (v3.0.2). Zenodo.
https://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7199437

**wordfreq data sources:**
- Google Books Ngrams and Google Books Syntactic Ngrams
- The Leeds Internet Corpus from the University of Leeds Centre for Translation Studies
- Wikipedia
- ParaCrawl, a multilingual Web crawl
- OPUS OpenSubtitles 2018, originating from OpenSubtitles
- SUBTLEX word lists (SUBTLEX-US, SUBTLEX-UK, SUBTLEX-CH, SUBTLEX-DE, and SUBTLEX-NL)
  created by Marc Brysbaert et al.

For full wordfreq license details, see: https://github.com/rspeer/wordfreq
